This paper proposes a new method for approximate sampling from Determinantal Point Processes (DPPs), which are probabilistic models of repulsion and diversity over discrete sets of items. The paper focuses on the efficiency of the sampling algorithm, which is important for large data sets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with the development of algorithms and models for large-scale data analysis. The paper also involves constructing coresets, which is a technique used in computational geometry and optimization, suggesting that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper involves probabilistic modeling, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves matrix operations, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Systems and Control).
